context:
Procedures Performed

1. Functional endoscopic sinus surgery.   2. Excision of nasopharyngeal mass via endoscopic technique.   3. Excision of right upper lid skin lesion 1 cm in diameter with adjacent tissue transfer closure.
The patient is a 51-year-old Caucasian female
patient's chief complaint of nasal congestion
patient's chief complaint of nasal congestion and chronic ear disease.
The patient also has had this right upper lid skin lesion which appears to be a cholesterol granuloma for numerous months.
The patient had a severely deviated nasal septum more so to the right than the left.
There appeared to be a spur on the left inferior aspect and also on the right posterior aspect.
The nasopharyngeal mass appeared polypoid in nature almost lymphoid tissue looking.
followed by bilateral Merocels and bacitracin-coated ointment.
The patient will be sent home with a prescription for Keflex 500 mg one p.o. b.i.d
The patient will be sent home with a prescription for Keflex 500 mg one p.o. b.i.d, and Tylenol #3 one to two p.o. q.4-6h. pain #30.
